<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-08-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-08-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="386" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d386">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">504.418B1/204</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Atherton</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 1635</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-08-16">August 16,
                                1935</date>.<lb/>[Received August 23.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to refer to the
                            Department’s instruction No. 938 of August 2, 1935, concerning the
                            Roerich Pact and directing the Embassy to inquire orally at the Foreign
                            Office the view with which it is disposed to regard this Convention.</p>
                        <p>In reply to an inquiry in the sense of the Department’s instruction, the
                            Foreign Office said that they had been made aware of the Pact and, after
                            considering it, do not feel at present that it is necessary for Great
                            Britain to accede.</p>
                        <p>Respectfully yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Ray Atherton</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>